{
  "texts": [
    "Now, the idea of the algorithm is, roughly speaking, that it is possible to use ℓ to transport the Stokes data of (E, ∇) and obtain those of (E, ∇).",
    "In order to give a precise formulation of this idea, one needs to describe the formal data and the Stokes data of connections in a suitable way.",
    "The description we use is as follows:",
    "• The formal data of (E, ∇) are encoded by a formal local system, which is a local system (of finite-dimensional vector spaces) V 0 on ∂ graded by I (see §2.2).",
    "-Those circles in I such that the corresponding graded parts of V 0 do not vanish are called the active circles or active exponents of (E, ∇)."
  ]
}